liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: After a blistering start, they've got the goal with a nice play. Hanane Ait El Haj sent the cross in from the right and Ibtissam Jraïdi raced to meet it at the near post, angling a header past the keeper. Historic goal, the first for Morocco at the Women's World Cup. Bernadette Clarke: "The Moroccan team celebrate right in front of their fans who are a lot louder now."
